@codebytere I think this problem might be on the Electron side anyway, see: https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src.git/+/61.0.3163.100/chrome/browser/speech/tts_win.cc#191

It has been fixed in a version prior to Chromium 61.0.3163.100 (not pinpointed the exact version yet), which is the version the current Electron beta uses.

But in the Electron beta source there seems to be a vendored version of this file, which has the old work around returning "native" instead of the actual speech languages: https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/2-0-x/chromium_src/chrome/browser/speech/tts_win.cc#L174

issue.body:
The implementation of tts_win.cc was brought up-to-speed with Chromium 70.0.3522.1 (https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src.git/+/70.0.3522.1/chrome/browser/speech/tts_win.cc).

This to solve the issue with no voices being returned on Windows (#11585).

Ping @AlbrechtStriffler

